        "name": "Tradespeople",
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "Common Artisan Guilds",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 244",
                  "aonid": 22,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 244",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                "page": 244,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Cartographers   \nCobblers   \nCooks and bakers   \nGlassblowers   \nHerbalists   \nJewelers and gem cutters   \nLeatherworkers   \nLocksmiths   \nMagecrafters   \nMasons and stonecutters   \nPainters and sign makers  \nPhysicians and apothecaries   \nPotion brewers   \nPotters   \nScroll keepers   \nShipwrights and sailmakers   \nSkinners and tanners   \nWagonmakers and wheelwrights   \nWeaponsmiths   \nWandcrafters   \nWeavers   \nWoodcarvers and coopers",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "link": {
              "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 244",
              "aonid": 22,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 244",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
            "page": 244,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Every settlement needs tradespeople to create new products, facilitate commerce, and keep the infrastructure from crumbling. Larger cities often have entire guilds dedicated to the creation of specific goods, managing worker conditions, and working with local governments.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
